abstract: Toyota said that net profit from July through September rose 11 percent from the period a year earlier, to 450.9 billion yen (nearly $4 billion).
snippet: Toyota said that net profit from July through September rose 11 percent from the period a year earlier, to 450.9 billion yen (nearly $4 billion).
lead_paragraph: TOKYO, Nov. 7 — Another quarter of higher profit at Toyota, Japan’s largest automaker, showed Wednesday that the company’s growth remained strong despite soaring global fuel prices and hints of an economic slowdown in its biggest market, the United States.

headline.main: Recent Dings Don’t Dent Toyota Profit
headline.print_headline: Recent Dings Don’t Dent Toyota Profit
